# Local secret/PII denylist for scripts/scan-secrets.mjs — NEVER COMMITTED.
#
# Copy this file to `.secret-scan-local.txt` (which is gitignored) and add, one
# per line, any literal strings the scanner should flag if they ever appear in a
# tracked file: your personal domains, real email addresses, account IDs, etc.
#
# Keeping these here (instead of in the committed scanner) means the values that
# identify you never get published, while your own commits are still checked
# against them.
#
# Example (replace with your own; these are illustrative): allowlist-secret
# mypersonaldomain.example
# my.real.address@somewhere.example  (illustrative only) allowlist-secret
